(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cairo &mdash; Egypt's official news agency said a Cairo Criminal Court has convicted and sentenced former Information Minister Safwat el-Sharif and two of his sons for corruption to between five and 10 years in prison.The MENA news agency reported on Saturday that el-Sharif and his son Ihab were each sentenced to five years. El-Sharif's second son, Ashraf, was sentenced to 10 years in absentia. The court fined all three a total of 209 million Egyptian pounds, about $24m.The court said el-Sharif had abused his power and together with his sons illegally amassed huge amounts of money, along with real estate.El-Sharif served as information minister and later as speaker of the parliament's upper chamber, or Shura Council.He was close to deposed autocratic President Hosni Mubarak.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.